The paper deals with learning latent-variable probabilistic graphical models, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new algorithm for learning and inference, which involves message-passing and junction trees, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) possible sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper deals with statistical consistency and correctness of the proposed algorithm, which falls under the scope of cs.IT (Information Theory).
